WEBVTT

00:01.691 --> 00:03.486
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:03.520 --> 00:11.494
♪♪

00:11.528 --> 00:19.571
♪♪

00:21.987 --> 00:26.543
♪♪

00:26.578 --> 00:28.890
[ Calm music playing overhead ]

00:28.925 --> 00:30.409
♪♪

00:30.444 --> 00:32.273
[ Breathing heavily]

00:32.308 --> 00:34.241
[ Dramatic music plays ]

00:34.275 --> 00:41.558
♪♪

00:41.593 --> 00:42.697
[ Gasps ]

00:42.732 --> 00:44.906
[ Grunts ]
[ Screams ]

00:44.941 --> 00:45.976
[ Grunts ]

00:46.011 --> 00:47.047
Now!
Huh?

00:47.081 --> 00:52.086
♪♪

00:52.121 --> 00:53.846
Ow.

00:53.881 --> 00:56.056
♪♪

00:56.090 --> 00:57.402
[ Grunting ]

00:57.436 --> 00:59.369
[ Darwin screams ]

00:59.404 --> 01:01.268
[ Richard screams ]

01:01.302 --> 01:02.786
[ All grunt ]

01:02.821 --> 01:04.478
♪♪

01:04.512 --> 01:05.651
Ow!
[ Grunts ]

01:05.686 --> 01:07.550
Hyah!
[ Grunts ]

01:07.584 --> 01:10.932
[ Roars ]

01:10.967 --> 01:12.727
Why can't we
just have one treat?

01:12.762 --> 01:14.764
Because it's the end
of the month, and I
work a dead-end job

01:14.798 --> 01:16.766
where I get paid
peanuts.[ All sigh ]

01:16.800 --> 01:18.250
That's not a figure of speech,
by the way.

01:18.285 --> 01:19.734
Then why are we
even here?

01:19.769 --> 01:22.323
Because I asked for an advance
on my next quarter,

01:22.358 --> 01:23.600
and they said, "Yes."

01:23.635 --> 01:25.119
Great!
I know a place

01:25.154 --> 01:27.466
where we can get a full
shopping cart for 25 cents.

01:27.501 --> 01:29.123
It's called the 1860s.

01:29.158 --> 01:31.229
But not if you're shopping
for a good deal.

01:31.263 --> 01:32.575
[ Sniffing ]

01:32.609 --> 01:34.646
-What's she doing?
-Sniffing out a bargain.

01:34.680 --> 01:35.888
Your mom's family
always had

01:35.923 --> 01:37.614
this super ability
to save money.

01:37.649 --> 01:40.134
I mean, she had a bowl haircut
until she was 6,

01:40.169 --> 01:42.309
but her parents didn't want
to wear down a good bowl,

01:42.343 --> 01:43.655
so technically,
she had

01:43.689 --> 01:46.278
a "doing a handstand
in a pothole" haircut.

01:46.313 --> 01:47.486
[ Sniffing ]

01:47.521 --> 01:49.039
Aisle 13.

01:50.351 --> 01:51.456
Ha-ha-ha!

01:51.490 --> 01:52.905
[ Grunts ]

01:52.940 --> 01:54.183
Corned beef.

01:54.217 --> 01:55.391
"This can can be opened

01:55.425 --> 01:56.909
by women of reasonable
intelligence

01:56.944 --> 01:58.601
with limited
male supervision"?

01:58.635 --> 02:00.534
Well, they're from
the '60s, but look,

02:00.568 --> 02:02.777
only 20 cents
for the whole pallet.

02:02.812 --> 02:04.641
I guess times
were easier then

02:04.676 --> 02:06.436
if you were a man
and not a minority

02:06.471 --> 02:07.713
and were comfortable
with the constant threat

02:07.748 --> 02:09.094
of nuclear
annihilation.

02:09.129 --> 02:10.992
Ha, how things
have changed, huh?

02:11.027 --> 02:12.408
All: Mm...

02:12.442 --> 02:13.512
[ Dejectedly ]
Yeah.

02:13.547 --> 02:14.755
Hey. Hey!

02:14.789 --> 02:16.515
This is our food
for the next month.

02:16.550 --> 02:18.138
Man: Back off, lady!
We saw it first.

02:18.172 --> 02:19.104
I grabbed it
first!

02:19.139 --> 02:21.279
Just leave it already.
It's ours!

02:21.313 --> 02:22.935
[ Grunts ]

02:25.214 --> 02:26.525
[ Gasps ]

02:27.250 --> 02:28.389
Dad?

02:28.424 --> 02:29.804
Mom?

02:30.564 --> 02:32.221
Oh, I can't believe it!Yeah.

02:32.255 --> 02:35.224
You'd think that finding
a tooth in this can
would've put me off,

02:35.258 --> 02:37.053
and yet --
I meant

02:37.087 --> 02:39.469
how could you kids
invite them to the house?

02:39.504 --> 02:41.437
Because we
deserve it, Mom.

02:41.471 --> 02:42.783
Think of it
as a gift to us.

02:42.817 --> 02:44.267
[ Sighs ] True.

02:44.302 --> 02:46.614
I can't deny you the right
to know your grandparents

02:46.649 --> 02:47.753
just because of a grudge.

02:47.788 --> 02:49.445
What? No! I meant
that they owe us

02:49.479 --> 02:50.963
hundreds of
Christmas presents.

02:50.998 --> 02:53.138
I really thought
I raised my children better.

02:53.173 --> 02:55.209
Yeah, you're right.
I'm sorry.

02:55.244 --> 02:56.969
We'd profit much more
if they bought

02:57.004 --> 02:58.523
one awesome,
huge, lump present

02:58.557 --> 03:00.110
instead of a bunch
of crummy ones.

03:00.145 --> 03:01.388
[ Sighs ]

03:01.422 --> 03:04.977
Come on. Let's give this
another chance.
Okay.

03:05.012 --> 03:07.014
Just promise me
you'll be good this time.

03:07.048 --> 03:09.223
I can't
just promise that.

03:09.258 --> 03:10.638
Why won't you
open up?

03:10.673 --> 03:12.261
There's so much
bad history between us.

03:12.295 --> 03:15.056
I mean, we stopped talking
over 20 years ago.

03:15.091 --> 03:17.714
Why are you always
so hard inside?

03:17.749 --> 03:19.406
I guess it's a way
to protect myself, but...

03:19.440 --> 03:20.752
[Sighs] you're right.

03:20.786 --> 03:23.133
I'll try my best
to be open.

03:23.168 --> 03:24.721
Thank you, Richard.

03:25.446 --> 03:26.654
Uh...[ Bolt clatters ]

03:26.689 --> 03:28.000
...anytime?

03:32.212 --> 03:34.628
[ Clock ticking ]

03:41.807 --> 03:44.465
[ Muffled ]
The atmosphere is so thick
you could cut it with a knife.

03:44.500 --> 03:46.191
[ Muffled ]
What?
Oh, hang on.

03:48.020 --> 03:49.470
[ Louder ] I said,
"The atmosphere is so thick

03:49.505 --> 03:51.300
you could
cut it with a knife."

03:51.334 --> 03:53.509
Maybe I'll join them
and try to lighten the mood.

03:53.543 --> 03:55.718
[ Pop ][ Grunts ]

03:55.752 --> 03:57.513
Hey, how about
a joke?

03:57.547 --> 03:59.722
I like my coffee
the way I like jokes

03:59.756 --> 04:01.655
about the way
I like my coffee.

04:01.689 --> 04:03.173
I don't.
[ Chuckles ]

04:04.382 --> 04:05.762
[ Glass breaks, screaming ]

04:05.797 --> 04:08.144
Wow, that's the second worst
that joke ever went down.

04:08.178 --> 04:10.560
It's not you, son.
They just blame each other

04:10.595 --> 04:11.941
for what happened
between them,

04:11.975 --> 04:13.805
but no one really knows
whose fault it is.

04:13.839 --> 04:15.738
It's like "potato,"
"potart-wah."

04:15.772 --> 04:16.980
Who's to say
which is wrong?

04:17.015 --> 04:18.637
There's only one way
to find out.

04:18.672 --> 04:20.708
Of course.
A backyard royal rumble.

04:20.743 --> 04:22.676
Last one standing
gets to name the vegetable.

04:22.710 --> 04:25.265
I mean we ask Mrs. Mom,
Grandpa Daniel,

04:25.299 --> 04:27.128
and Granny Mary
to air their issues,

04:27.163 --> 04:29.096
and we'll decide
who's in the wrong.

04:29.130 --> 04:31.029
And then we --It's pronounced
"potato,"

04:31.063 --> 04:32.651
and no one's doing
a Canadian Destroyer

04:32.686 --> 04:34.204
off a shed
in the backyard.

04:34.239 --> 04:35.723
Oh...

04:37.967 --> 04:40.314
Okay, I'll start.
[ Inhales deeply ]

04:40.349 --> 04:42.799
You have always
been disappointed in me.

04:42.834 --> 04:44.939
Only because
we loved you.
No!

04:44.974 --> 04:47.563
Because you always had
insane expectations for me.

04:47.597 --> 04:48.840
Like how you
made me wear

04:48.874 --> 04:50.842
those ridiculous clothes
my whole life.

04:50.876 --> 04:52.844
In life you have to dress
for the job you want.

04:52.878 --> 04:55.605
Don't you think you started
a little early?

04:55.640 --> 04:57.331
Congratulations
to both of you.

04:57.366 --> 04:58.436
It's a...
-[ Coos ]

04:58.470 --> 04:59.713
...CEO?

04:59.747 --> 05:01.335
Well, you were hardly
easy yourself.

05:01.370 --> 05:04.338
Remember that finger painting
you did for Mother's Day?

05:04.373 --> 05:05.926
Hmm?

05:05.960 --> 05:07.099
Ah.

05:09.101 --> 05:09.999
[ Sighs ]

05:10.033 --> 05:11.483
Well, maybe
it all comes back

05:11.518 --> 05:13.140
to the stupid name
you gave me.

05:13.174 --> 05:15.211
Uh, what's wrong
with "Nicole"?

05:15.245 --> 05:16.833
"Nicole"
is my middle name.

05:16.868 --> 05:18.594
My first name
is "Doctor."

05:18.628 --> 05:19.940
[ Stifled laughter ]

05:19.974 --> 05:21.769
Oh, it's all very funny
until someone shouts,

05:21.804 --> 05:24.738
"Is there a doctor in
the house," and your
parents say, "Yes."

05:24.772 --> 05:26.464
Turns out people choking
on a chicken wing

05:26.498 --> 05:29.087
rarely stay conscious
long enough to enjoy
the punch line.

05:29.121 --> 05:30.882
But we only wanted
the best for you.

05:30.916 --> 05:33.125
What? Like the time I needed
a blood transfusion

05:33.160 --> 05:34.817
and you gave me
the wrong blood type?

05:34.851 --> 05:37.406
Why settle for B-
when you can have A+?

05:37.440 --> 05:39.339
Nothing was ever enough!

05:39.373 --> 05:41.893
You forced me to join
a gazillion after-school clubs.

05:41.927 --> 05:44.723
We gave you every possible
chance to succeed.

05:44.758 --> 05:47.001
Yeah! All at
the same time!

05:47.036 --> 05:48.624
[ Playing violin ]

05:48.658 --> 05:49.832
[ Gasps ]

05:49.866 --> 05:51.385
[ Stops and resumes playing ]

05:51.420 --> 05:57.564
♪♪

05:57.598 --> 05:58.634
[ Stops playing ]

05:58.668 --> 05:59.876
[ Resumes playing ]

05:59.911 --> 06:01.291
[ Screams ]
Ha!

06:01.326 --> 06:02.879
[ Whistle blows ]
That's a foul, Doctor Nicole.

06:02.914 --> 06:04.605
Why?
It wasn't
a karate match.

06:04.640 --> 06:06.814
It was a drama-club rehearsal
of "Madame Butterfly."

06:06.849 --> 06:08.885
-[ Sighs ]
-Ha!

06:08.920 --> 06:10.128
That was the karate.

06:10.162 --> 06:11.957
What kind of childhood
was that?

06:11.992 --> 06:13.545
I was only
eight years old.

06:13.580 --> 06:16.479
Well, at that age,
I was already 10.
[ Growls ]

06:16.514 --> 06:17.998
See?
That's your problem.

06:18.032 --> 06:19.724
You always let your anger
get the better of you.

06:19.758 --> 06:22.382
I spent years fixing the
consequences of your outbursts.

06:22.416 --> 06:24.763
Oh, please! There's nothing
a child can break

06:24.798 --> 06:26.247
that can't be fixed
with a bit of duct tape.

06:26.282 --> 06:28.905
What about the time
you kicked the neighbor's car?

06:31.287 --> 06:32.426
[ Gasps ]

06:33.496 --> 06:36.119
Come on,
I wasn't that bad.You kidding me?

06:36.154 --> 06:37.880
You landed a kid
in the hospital.

06:37.914 --> 06:39.916
[ Child screaming,
glass shatters ]

06:39.951 --> 06:41.470
Literally.
Not to mention the time

06:41.504 --> 06:43.506
you stole our car
to see your boyfriend

06:43.541 --> 06:45.128
and landed in court.

06:45.163 --> 06:47.337
[ Crowd gasps, Nicole grunts ]

06:47.372 --> 06:48.373
Crowd: Guilty!

06:48.408 --> 06:49.374
Oops.

06:49.409 --> 06:50.548
Again, literally.

06:50.582 --> 06:51.997
What else
was I supposed to do?

06:52.032 --> 06:53.896
You always disapproved
of Richard.

06:53.930 --> 06:55.587
You never thought
he was good enough for me.

06:55.622 --> 06:57.244
That's not true.

07:02.491 --> 07:05.252
Really? Still trying to set me
up with some banking dweeb?

07:05.286 --> 07:07.668
No offense, but we always
thought she could do better

07:07.703 --> 07:09.256
than a slacker
with a dead-end job

07:09.290 --> 07:11.776
who got their pants
at the Army surplus store

07:11.810 --> 07:13.916
in the parachute aisle.How dare you!

07:13.950 --> 07:17.126
My wife's behind is so small
only bats can hear her toot.

07:17.160 --> 07:19.542
I meant you.Then joke is on you.

07:19.577 --> 07:21.682
I don't have a job.
[ Sighs ]

07:21.717 --> 07:23.926
But did you really
have to walk out like that?

07:23.960 --> 07:25.548
I left because
there was no point

07:25.583 --> 07:28.413
in trying to fix something
that was beyond repair.

07:28.448 --> 07:31.381
I wanted to start over
and create something better.

07:31.416 --> 07:32.900
Us too,
but we were too old

07:32.935 --> 07:34.661
to have
another chiiiild --

07:34.695 --> 07:35.972
We have a dog now.

07:36.007 --> 07:37.940
[ Sighs ] You never even
came to our wedding.

07:37.974 --> 07:40.149
-We did. We went to Rsvp.
-What?

07:40.183 --> 07:42.807
On your invite,
it said, "Rsvp."No, Mom.

07:42.841 --> 07:44.878
It said, "RSVP."
-Oh, right.

07:44.912 --> 07:47.225
Well, we went to the town
of Rsvp in Moldavia.

07:47.259 --> 07:48.606
[ Dog barking ]I was the only woman
in the region.

07:48.640 --> 07:50.918
Everybody tried to marry me,
even a dog.

07:50.953 --> 07:52.506
Like I said,
we have a dog now.

07:52.541 --> 07:55.267
Wait, is that why you sent
Richard and I divorce papers

07:55.302 --> 07:57.787
for our first anniversary?
-No, that was because

07:57.822 --> 07:59.582
you sent me
retirement-home leaflets

07:59.617 --> 08:00.997
for my 50th birthday...

08:01.032 --> 08:02.827
[ Party horn honks ]...with glitter!

08:02.861 --> 08:04.414
Well, that's because
you tried to ship

08:04.449 --> 08:05.933
Richard to Guatemala!

08:07.176 --> 08:09.834
Daniel:
No, that was after you took
power of attorney over us

08:09.868 --> 08:12.008
and got us committed
for six weeks!

08:12.043 --> 08:14.252
No, that was after
you paid for our honeymoon,

08:14.286 --> 08:16.565
but replaced Richard
with a neurosurgeon.

08:16.599 --> 08:18.670
Well, that
was after --

08:18.705 --> 08:20.258
After...

08:20.292 --> 08:21.466
Uh...

08:21.501 --> 08:22.916
Uh...Mm.

08:23.675 --> 08:25.332
I don't remember.

08:25.366 --> 08:26.540
Me neither.

08:26.575 --> 08:28.646
Then why are you still
angry at each other?

08:28.680 --> 08:30.406
Why can't you
just make peace?

08:30.440 --> 08:32.926
We were at peace,
Darwin,

08:32.960 --> 08:34.548
separately.

08:34.583 --> 08:36.585
[ Solemn music plays ]

08:36.619 --> 08:38.725
♪♪

08:38.759 --> 08:40.002
[ Sighs ] Okay.

08:40.036 --> 08:41.486
I know this is
the cheapest,

08:41.521 --> 08:43.868
dirtiest kind
of emotional manipulation,

08:43.902 --> 08:46.456
but there's too much
on the line here, so...

08:47.906 --> 08:51.876
♪ 10,000 reasons to give up

08:51.910 --> 08:55.017
♪ Too many words that piled up

08:55.051 --> 08:56.225
I think
we should go.

08:56.259 --> 09:00.298
♪ But you refuse
to try and mend

09:00.332 --> 09:04.578
♪ Your broken past
before the end ♪

09:04.613 --> 09:08.617
♪ Your heart's
too hard to understand ♪

09:08.651 --> 09:12.759
♪ That sands of time
slip through your hands ♪

09:12.793 --> 09:17.177
♪ And no excuses can erase

09:17.211 --> 09:20.870
♪ The scars of time
left on your face ♪

09:20.905 --> 09:24.218
♪ If it's too hard to forgive

09:24.253 --> 09:27.359
♪ Then just give

09:27.394 --> 09:32.468
♪ Let go of the weight
that won't let you live ♪

09:32.502 --> 09:36.265
♪♪

09:36.299 --> 09:40.372
♪ Why keep playing
this sad game ♪

09:40.407 --> 09:44.584
♪ Of who should really
take the blame? ♪

09:44.618 --> 09:48.657
♪ The memories will fade away

09:48.691 --> 09:52.833
♪ They're growing
further every day ♪

09:52.868 --> 09:57.217
♪ You want the stream
to change its course ♪

09:57.251 --> 10:01.497
♪ Before it floods you
with remorse ♪

10:01.531 --> 10:05.328
♪ You only need
to hit the brakes ♪

10:05.363 --> 10:09.298
♪ To free yourself
of your mistakes ♪

10:09.332 --> 10:12.922
♪ If it's too hard to forgive

10:12.957 --> 10:15.753
♪ Then just give

10:15.787 --> 10:20.930
♪ Let go of the weight
that won't let you live ♪

10:20.965 --> 10:22.276
♪♪

10:22.311 --> 10:24.451
[ Car approaching ]

10:24.485 --> 10:28.904
♪♪

10:28.938 --> 10:32.148
Nicole, I --Look, I don't want to hear
your excuses.

10:33.494 --> 10:35.738
I just want
you guys back.

10:35.773 --> 10:36.912
[ Car doors open ]

10:36.946 --> 10:41.088
♪ Mm, mm, mm-mm, mm

10:41.123 --> 10:43.988
♪ Mm, mm, mm-mm, mm

10:44.022 --> 10:45.575
[ Song ends ]

10:45.610 --> 10:46.853
Well done,
Gumball.

10:46.887 --> 10:49.821
You really summed up their
relationship with each other

10:49.856 --> 10:51.029
and helped them
reconnect.

10:51.064 --> 10:52.617
What's that now?
You know,

10:52.652 --> 10:55.275
"If it's too hard to forgive,
then just give."

10:55.309 --> 10:57.139
Pfft!
That wasn't about them.

10:57.173 --> 10:59.417
That was about the Christmas
presents they owe us.

11:00.383 --> 11:01.108
Aah!

11:02.662 --> 11:12.430
♪♪

11:12.464 --> 11:22.198
♪♪

11:22.233 --> 11:32.036
♪♪
